<%= ks_element :id => "mobile_usage",
              :data => {
                :container => "ipadish_content",
                :title => "MBSJ: #{t("dashboard.mobile_usage")}",
                :position => 20
              } do %>
  <div class="panel">
    <div style="float:right;width: 300px;height: 300px;background-color: #FFF;margin: 10px;border: solid 1px #000">
      <!-- http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?chs=200x200&cht=qr&chl=http%3a//mbsj2012.castle104.com -->
      <%= image_tag('galapagos_qr.png') %>
    </div>

    <h2>Using this site from smartphones (iPhone, iPod Touch and Android)</h2>
    <p>Participants using either iPhone, iPod Touch or Android devices will be redirected to the smartphone-optimized website. Please access this site via the link below or the QR code on the right.</p>
    <p>The smartphone-optimized website offers the same features as this PC website. "Likes" and "My Schedules" will be visible from all devices.</p>
    <p>We suggest that you set your "Likes" and "My Schedule" from the comfort of your PC, and use your smartphone to view them at the conference hall.</p>
    <h2>Using this site from feature phones (iMode, EZweb, etc.)</h2>
    <p>Participants using feature phones (iMode, EZweb, etc.) will be redirected to the feature-phone optimized website. Please access this site via the link below or the QR code on the right.</p>
    <p>The feature-phone optimized website offers the same features as this PC website with the exception of the graphically challenging timetable and poster map. "Likes" and "My Schedules" will be visible from all devices.</p>
    <p>We suggest that you set your "Likes" and "My Schedule" from the comfort of your PC, and use your feature-phone to view them at the conference hall.</p>
    <h2>Using this site from iPad and other tablet devices</h2>
    <p>Since iPad provides enough screen space to sufficiently display the PC website, it will be directed to the PC site.</p>
    <p>Android tablets generally have smaller screen sizes and therefore are directed to the smartphone-optimized website.</p>
    <h2>Supported browsers on the PC website</h2>
    <p>This website is optimized for newer versions of Safari, Firefox, Chrome and Internet Explorer 10. This website uses cutting-edge browser technology to provide offline viewing etc. and we strongly suggest that you use these browsers. Internet Explorer 9 is also supported without animations. Internet Explorer 8 is supported but features such as offline viewing will not be available.</p>
    <p>Unsupported browsers will automatically be directed to the feature-phone optimized website.</p>
    <br />
    <%= link_to "mbsj2012.castle104.com", "http://mbsj2012.castle104.com" %>
    <div style="clear:both"></div>
  </div>
    <%= render :partial => 'layouts/biokaimono' %>
<% end %>